  "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
  "active_lock_reason": null,
  "body": "We currently use CodeCov.io to display code coverage in the repo however that only measures **line coverage**. Line based coverage reporting is less informative than branch coverage ie. in this example, if `something == false` is never tested, the line coverage score will be 80%, but the branch coverage score will be 50%.\r\n\r\n```\r\nif(something){\r\n   line1;\r\n   line2;\r\n   line3;\r\n   line4;\r\n} else {\r\n   line5;\r\n}\r\n```\r\n\r\nWe may not be able to do branch based coverage with CodeCov.io, but we should investigate and look at the alternatives. Also consider how the codecov report ties in with the more detailed `solidity-coverage` reports we have. Are they overlapping? Do we need both?",
